description: There’s nothing better than an easy traybake packed with big Mediterranean flavours. This recipe of basa fillets, potatoes, onion, tomato and olives is super easy to prepare, but will certainly impress family or guests.
keywords: Fish dishes,Pescatarian,Gluten free,Egg free,Seafood,Traybake,Sesame free,Budget,Seafood dishes,Fresh Ideas magazine,Soy free,Wheat free,Nikki P,Tomato,Peanut free
name: Fish With Tomato & Olive Traybake Recipe | Woolworths

recipeInstructions.text: Preheat oven to 230°C/210°C fan-forced. Grease a large baking tray. Place potatoes in a large bowl. Add oil and toss to coat. Arrange potato on tray. Bake for 20 minutes or until golden.

Add tomato, onion and olives to tray. Pat fish dry with paper towel. Arrange fish over vegetables and top with lemon slices. Sprinkle with fennel seeds and season with pepper. Bake for a further 15 minute or until fish is cooked through. Sprinkle with parsley. Serve.
